{"APSE":[{"def":"A reliquary, or case in which the relics of saints were kept.","pos":""}],"APSIDAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the apsides of an orbit.","pos":""},{"def":"Of or pertaining to the apse of a church; as, the apsidal termination of the chancel.","pos":""}],"APSIS":[{"def":"One of the two points of an orbit, as of a planet or satellite, which are at the greatest and least distance from the central body, corresponding to the aphelion and perihelion of a planet, or to the apogee and perigee of the moon.","pos":""},{"def":"In a curve referred to polar coördinates, any point for which the radius vector is a maximum or minimum.","pos":""}]}